│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation happens because in the vector-early-exit path, exit PHIs are fed with a scalar      │
│ index (%offset.idx) from the vector body without extracting the active lane, yielding the wrong value (0        │
│ instead of 1 in the reproducer). The code only inserts an ExtractLane when the VF range clamps to vectors,      │
│ which may skip extraction if scalar VF is included. To fix, always perform lane extraction for non-live-in      │
│ incoming values from the early exit, regardless of the VF range, so the PHIs get the correct lane value under   │
│ early exit.                                                                                                     │
